Three houses belonging to politicians including that of an MEC economic development Sello Lehare have been torched.The supply of running water has been a burning issue for some time for the communities near Hammanskraal in the North West with the municipality admitting last year that it could not meet an estimated 25% of demand.Moretele is also one of several municipalities that owe Tshwane millions of rands for water and have been cut off for lack of payment.The latest dispute arose when arrangements for a planned meeting in Tshwane between officials and residents did not materialise as promised.Enraged the residents blocked roads. Security guards were accused of fatally shooting a resident during the fracas. Residents then went on rampage burning down the houses.This is a developing story and will be updated when we receive more information.- TMG Digital/TimesLIVE